<html><head></head><body style="word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space; ">Even though you think you do, you actually don't have the path set correctly on the Mac side. Remember, when executing from ssh, the .cshrc (or whatever shell you use) executes differently. So even though an interactive login gets the right path, the non-interactive execution doesn't.<div><br></div><div>See&nbsp;<a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/faq/?category=running#adding-ompi-to-path">http://www.open-mpi.org/faq/?category=running#adding-ompi-to-path</a> for details</div><div><br></div><div><br><div><div>On Jul 19, 2012, at 9:13 PM, christophe petit wrote:</div><br class="Apple-interchange-newline"><blockquote type="cite">Hello,<br><br>I try to launch an executable on 2 computers ( Debian 6.0 and MacOS snow leopard ).<br><br>I have successfully installed on both Open-MPI 1.6 with the option "--enable-heterogenous" and<br>setup passwordless ssh connection between the 2 computers.<br>
<br>My issue is that the <span class="b5">distributed co</span><span class="b4">mputing</span> works fine but only when I launch the <br>"mpirun -np 16 -hostfile hosts.txt program_exec" command from the MacOS computer, not from Debian pc.<br>
